---
import ContactLayout from '~/layouts/ContactLayout.astro';

const metadata = { title: 'Request Private Beta Access', description: 'Request Private Beta Access | Archodex' };

const CONTACT_US_MESSAGE = `Hi Archodex Team!

I would like to request access to the Archodex private beta.

<Optionally, tell us more about your use case, environment, etc.>
`;
---

<ContactLayout title="Real protection for AI, no security theater." prefill={CONTACT_US_MESSAGE} metadata={metadata}>
  <section class="relative">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-5 pb-10 md:pb-14 space-y-4">
      <p>
        Archodex observes and protects AI activity across the host OS, inside devcontainers and container VMs, and in
        compute clusters. It can enforce policy to allow, block, redact, and tokenize sensitive data before risky
        activity turns into data leakage or unauthorized actions.
      </p>
      <p>
        What makes Archodex different is coverage. We can see the full payloads of LLM and agentic network requests,
        including tool-driven access to internal and external services, even when those channels are protected with TLS.
        There are no MITM proxies, no certificate management burden, and no breakage from mTLS or cert pinning.
      </p>

      <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3 mt-8 text-center">
        <div
          class="rounded-lg border border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700 px-5 bg-primary/5 dark:bg-white/5 py-5"
        >
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold font-heading mb-2">Individual Builders</h3>
          <p>
            Start from a safe default. Archodex blocks authenticated traffic and read-write operations out of the box,
            then gives you fine-grained control to allow, block, redact, or tokenize access to external and internal
            services.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div
          class="rounded-lg border border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700 px-5 bg-primary/5 dark:bg-white/5 py-5"
        >
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold font-heading mb-2">Security and Platform Teams</h3>
          <p>
            Enable AI usage without losing visibility or control. Archodex delivers centralized, endpoint-level coverage
            across local machines, containers, and clusters where proxy-based and domain-based approaches leave gaps.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div
          class="rounded-lg border border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700 px-5 bg-primary/5 dark:bg-white/5 py-5"
        >
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold font-heading mb-2">Advanced Agent Workloads</h3>
          <p>
            Archodex fills a gap in projects like NVIDIA NemoClaw / OpenShell. These projects sandbox local resource
            access, but do not have network protection by default because of complications with MITM proxying. Archodex
            can be layered on top.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</ContactLayout>
